724225f-a.text:
Washington Street, west side, north from clearing adjoining and at the S.W. corner of 13th Street. These last two blocks of Washington Street, which are parallel to Ninth Avenue, vere only cut through from Little West 12th to 14th Streets about 1890, probably to expedite traffic bound for the new West Washington Market, between
West Strect and Thirteenth avenue.
July 28, 1931.
P. L. Sperr.
